| Command                                                            | Meaning                                  |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------- |
| `git status`                                                       | Shows what's changed                     |
| `git add .`                                                        | Stages changes for the next commit       |
| `git commit -m "Create bootcamp folder structure and Day 1 notes"` | Saves a snapshot of your work locally    |
| `git push`                                                         | Uploads your commits to GitHub           |
| `git pull`                                                         | Downloads the latest changes from GitHub |

Save and Exit --> Press the Esc key. --> Type: `:wq`
Cancel the commit --> If you don't want to commit right now: --> Press Esc --> Type: `:q!`

